Title: Human oral bioavailability prediction
Description: Prediction of human oral bioavailability for small molecules. Given SMILES, the HobPre model predicts the Human oral bioavailability (HOB) value (two cutoffs of 20% and 50% for classification of molecules). The prediction is either high or low HOB.
Interpretation: This model takes smiles as input and outputs the Probability(high) of human-oral-bioavailability(HOB) for both the 20% cutoff and that of 50% cutoff.  The first value is the probability of HOB being high at 20% cutoff and the second value is the probability of HOB being high at 50% cutoff.
